Sentencas: The time-dependent degradation of the oxygen exchange kinetics of the solid oxide fuel cell cathode material La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is investigated at 600 degrees C. Special emphasis is placed on systematic long-term dc-conductivity relaxation measurements (t>1000 h) in dry as well as in humidified atmospheres in order to obtain representative trends for the application of LSCF in intermediate-temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: The determination of the chemical surface exchange coefficient k(chem) of oxygen is combined with investigations of the elemental surface compositions and depth profiles of fresh and degraded samples by X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS), providing further insight into the mechanisms of degradation.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: The slow decrease of k(chem) by a factor of 2 during exposure of the sample to a dry O-2-Ar reference atmosphere for 1000 h at 600 degrees C can be ascribed to an enrichment of La and Sr in correlation with an elevated oxygen concentration within about 30-35 nm depth.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: The interpretation of the XPS core level spectra indicates the formation of SrO and La2O3 secondary phases in this zone.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: The subsequent treatment in a humidified atmosphere for 1000 h results in a pronounced initial decrease of k(chem) by an additional factor of 10, followed by a time dependent decay of about 15% kh(-1)
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: A Sr-rich silicate layer of about 10 nm thickness is identified by XPS as the major cause of the degradation in humidified atmosphere.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: The evidence of Si-poisoning over the whole sample surface could also be confirmed by post-test SEM analysis.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: In addition, indications of a restructuring of the sample surface during the degradation are shown.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: These results indicate, that with LSCF as a cathode in ambient (humid) air in SOFC stacks containing various Si-sources, such as glass or glass-ceramic seals, and thermal insulation materials a significant decrease of the surface oxygen exchange coefficient can occur, even at temperatures as low as 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: In order to prevent a severe Si-induced degradation, dry air should be used as an oxidant.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres

Sentencas: However, even in dry atmosphere a minor decrease of k(chem) can occur during long-term operation due to changes in the relative cation and oxygen content at the surface.
Titulo: Oxygen exchange kinetics of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 at 600 °C in dry and humid atmospheres
